description._content: Description: Tractor sown area of 1926, showing Acacia cyanophylla most severely damaged by browsing of goats in 1933, although reserved against grazing, Xylotymbo Forest, Elevation 180 feet. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Description: Avenue of Eucalytus tereticornis, Laxia tou Spyrou, planted in 1926, Age 7 years, Xylotymbo Forest, Elevation 180 feet above sea level. Location: Cyprus Date: 1920-1939 Our Catalogue Reference: Part of CO 1069/698 This image is part of the Colonial Office photographic collection held at The National Archives.
